Author: KomodoWorld#8282
Content: I didn't understand a part:

Author: KomodoWorld#8282
Content: is the KMDCC chain a parallel chain on the same KMD cluster using the burn protocol to move coins between the chains?

Author: KomodoWorld#8282
Content: Or it is a pegged sidechain, i.e. the coins are locked on the KMD chain via Gateway CC and 1:1 pegged coins created on the other chain? I read the latter case but I found the terminology confusing.

Author: KomodoWorld#8282
Content: Or has the tech evolved and blurred the distinction between such cases? I try my best to stay updated but really it isn't clear

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: we are working on an -ac_import functionality that will utilize gateways, but instead of making a token, it uses the crosschain import mechanism to create new coins

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: so it is a new thing that is a 1:1 sidechain

Author: KomodoWorld#8282
Content: ah a new thing

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: and a gateways multisig deposit will be used to create KMDCC automatically

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: when the KMDCC is withdrawn, it will be burned and the msig KMD withdrawn to KMD

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: this creates a KMD 1:1 equivalent coin that is CC activated

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: as soon as KMDCC is finished, which I expect to be late Q1 or Q2, but no promises on dates yet

Author: KomodoWorld#8282
Content: ok understood

Author: KomodoWorld#8282
Content: it will be useful for marketing to explain the differences and how this evolved 🙂

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: so the KMDCC will be  a native coin on its own chain

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: CC can be made to work with tokens, but that requires custom work for each CC that wants to support them

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: so a need for a pure sidechain existed

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: -ac_import was what I came up with to solve this

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: that way all CC that works on the assetchains coin will work for KMD

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: well KMDCC, which can be 1:1 converted without any counterparty

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: So temporarily, we lose zaddr for KMD equivalent, but the reality was that only 0.1% was in use and this allows the rebrand message to be louder and clearer. no more can people just ignore KMD as being just another zcash fork

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: interesting thing is that KMD mainchain was before zcash mainchain

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: and I think I was the second one to fork the zcash repo, after one of their internal devs

Author: SHossain#0007
Content:
Anyone looking for wallet.dat security, now you have it. You can now encrypt wallet.dat with a secure password and keep your KMD secure. This is a CLI only function for now. If you use 
 Agama, you can access CLI from Settings. (don't encrypt your wallet.dat if you have z address in your wallet)
Encrypt wallet.dat guide: https://docs.komodoplatform.com/komodo/encrypt-wallet.html
Using CLI via Agama guide: https://support.komodoplatform.com/en/support/solutions/articles/29000026800-agama-desktop-cli-command-line-
